Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.80,0:00:02.27,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name's Conan Edogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.27,0:00:05.41,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}High school student Shin'ichi was forced to take a drug that shrunk him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.41,0:00:06.87,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Although smaller, my intelligence remains the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.87,0:00:08.74,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}I solve cases not even adults can!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:11.61,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sorry for the wait!\NToday's Conan is a one-hour special!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.61,0:00:13.38,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Multiple murders on a southern island!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.38,0:00:15.72,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The sad truth behind a piano sonata!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.38,0:02:04.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Why does the famous detective Kogoro Mouri\Nhave to go to a stupid island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.56,0:02:10.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,when he could be spending his time at a flower viewing party?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.46,0:02:14.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's all because of that letter I got a week ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.17,0:02:15.70,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}"On the night of the next full moon,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.70,0:02:18.70,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}"shadows will once again begin to disappear from Tsukikage Island."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:21.57,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Investigate. Keiji Aso."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.14,0:02:25.04,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mouri Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:27.48,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two days until the next full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.48,0:02:30.75,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've transferred half a million to your bank account.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.75,0:02:31.75,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}You had best come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.75,0:02:34.62,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on! Who the heck are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.62,0:02:38.49,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Keiji Aso from Tsukikage Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.49,0:02:41.73,Flashback,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, wait! Hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.73,0:02:45.10,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He didn't even bother for me to accept him as a client or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.10,0:02:46.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What's to complain about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.36,0:02:49.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,At least we get to relax on a small island near Izu!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.17,0:02:50.66,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.37,0:02:54.84,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Tsukikage Island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.34,0:02:58.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Keiji Aso...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.14,0:03:00.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I don't see anyone by that name in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:03.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Look harder, could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.35,0:03:05.98,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I have a letter from him right here, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.98,0:03:08.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But he's not in the list of residents,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.99,0:03:12.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and I just moved to this island, so I don't know that much about—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.16,0:03:13.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:19.26,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Chief, it seems that these people have been hired by a resident here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:20.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hired?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.03,0:03:23.47,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's right. By someone named Keiji Aso...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:27.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What? Did you say Keiji Aso?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:39.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's not possible!\NHe's been dead for over 10 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.02,0:03:50.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He was a famous pianist who was born and raised on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.23,0:03:54.37,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was the night of a full moon, 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.37,0:03:56.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was his first time home in a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.43,0:04:00.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,so he held a concert in the town's community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:03.71,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But afterwards, he suddenly shut his family and himself inside their home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.71,0:04:06.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and lit the place on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:09.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He allegedly stabbed his wife and daughter to death
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.78,0:04:13.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and then continued to play the piano as the fire raged on,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.65,0:04:16.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,almost as if he was possessed by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.89,0:04:21.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Beethoven's piano sonata... "Moonlight".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.33,0:04:28.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,A letter from a dead man...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.17,0:04:30.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What a nasty prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.17,0:04:31.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:37.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Your fee was paid, plus the letter was postmarked from this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.34,0:04:43.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I bet someone on the island wants you to look into Keiji Aso's affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.15,0:04:44.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:48.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The mayor here used to be a good friend of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.69,0:04:50.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Maybe he can tell us something!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:51.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:55.79,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They said the mayor's over at the community center, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.79,0:04:59.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Now then, Kenta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Make sure to keep warm when you sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.30,0:05:01.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ok, I will! Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:03.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:04.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:06.90,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Where is the community center?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.90,0:05:12.01,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You turn that corner and then keep going straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.01,0:05:14.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait, are you folks from Tokyo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:17.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's right. We got off the ship just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:19.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I live in Tokyo too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.78,0:05:22.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But this island is so much nicer,\Nwouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:26.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The air's fresh, and it's nice and quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:30.73,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Protect the island's fishing industry!\NVote for Masato Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:32.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Well, maybe not too quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.16,0:05:34.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The mayoral election is coming up, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:36.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The mayoral election, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.67,0:05:40.60,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The candidates are Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho represents the fishermen,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.60,0:05:44.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,current mayor Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwhose popularity is dwindling as of late,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:48.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nthe wealthiest man on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:50.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My patients have been telling me\Nthat Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:55.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's alright, Nurse. We're not really\Nthat interested in the election...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:59.60,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Doctor\NNarumi Asai (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:57.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's Doctor Narumi Asai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.99,0:05:59.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I have an actual license, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:02.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, you're a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:04.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,If you folks are headed to the community center,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:07.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,you can meet the three of them there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.33,0:06:10.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Tonight they're holding a 3rd-year memorial for Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:12.47,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,our previous mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:14.64,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Your previous mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:16.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,A 3rd-year memorial?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:18.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't let the mayor continue his reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.97,0:06:21.71,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't let the mayor continue his reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.71,0:06:23.88,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:28.09,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Current Mayor of Tsukikage Island\NTatsuji Kuroiwa (56)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.05,0:06:26.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,How dare they do this on the night
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,of the previous mayor's memorial?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:31.52,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They're really getting on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.59,0:06:32.30,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Kuroiwa's Only Daughter\NReiko Kuroiwa (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.52,0:06:32.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hirata!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.30,0:06:36.06,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What're you doing?!\NShut them up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.52,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Secretary to the Mayor\NKazuaki Hirata (31)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.52,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.86,0:06:41.83,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't let the mayor continue his reign of terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:43.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey, everything OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.53,0:06:45.37,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Is what OK, Shuuichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.37,0:06:46.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They're saying this election
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:49.49,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Reiko's Fiancé\NShuichi Murasawa (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.97,0:06:49.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,ain't looking so good for your old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:53.18,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Indeed. It would seem the citizens
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.74,0:06:54.80,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Wealthiest Man in Town\NHideo Kawashima (56)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:54.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,favor me the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:06:59.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's only because you know how to use money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.22,0:07:01.85,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Which I learned from you, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:04.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's a man here who wants to see the mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:06.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Who is it, at a time like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:09.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,A detective from Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.33,0:07:12.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What? A detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:17.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Come on, how long are they\Ngoing to make me wait?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.00,0:07:19.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:23.03,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}A piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:26.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Stop that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.51,0:07:30.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? What a huge room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.45,0:07:34.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So the rear of the community center is on the water's edge...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This piano sure is dirty...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:40.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You'd think they could at least clean it once in a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.39,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No, don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.39,0:07:50.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's the cursed piano that Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} played the day he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:53.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Cursed? Give me a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:55.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't the only one!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.44,0:07:58.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The same thing happened to the last mayor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:07:59.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You mean Isamu Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.81,0:08:02.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,the person they're holding the memorial for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.65,0:08:06.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. It happened 2 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.95,0:08:10.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was the night of a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.29,0:08:14.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I was passing by the community center,\Nwhich should have been empty,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.73,0:08:18.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,when I heard the sounds of\Na piano coming from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.23,0:08:22.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,When I called out to see who\Nwas there, the music stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.97,0:08:27.64,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Inside, I found Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.64,0:08:29.64,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He had died of a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.64,0:08:32.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And the music he had been playing before he died
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.58,0:08:37.98,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,was the same piece Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had performed in the fire: "Moonlight".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:44.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,After that, this piano came to\Nbe known as the Cursed Piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:48.26,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.26,0:08:51.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seems normal enough to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:57.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Anyway, please wait by the front\Ndoor until the memorial is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:09:00.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, you're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.34,0:09:02.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Narumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Are you going to the memorial?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:07.95,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the first person I autopsied when I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:10.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I thought I would burn some incense in his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.75,0:09:14.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, this is Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I happened to meet him on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.02,0:09:16.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hello, my name's Shimizu.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.22,0:09:18.38,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Mayoral Candidate\NMasato Shimizu (49)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.65,0:09:18.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:24.73,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Unemployed\NKen Nishimoto (55)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:26.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey, Kawashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.53,0:09:30.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You hired a detective to dig up\Nsome dirt on me, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.97,0:09:33.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.24,0:09:35.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Running away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.07,0:09:36.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:42.98,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:45.98,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That piano should have remained unused for years now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:48.19,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}but it produced a perfect sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:51.02,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Someone must be tuning it secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.02,0:09:53.16,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}For some purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.16,0:09:57.99,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}And what exactly was that letter trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:09.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This song!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:11.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...Moonlight! Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.74,0:10:13.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.08,0:10:17.01,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey! Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:22.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.99,0:10:25.01,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.83,0:10:29.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.99,0:10:31.66,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.66,0:10:35.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Ran. Contact the local police station!\N- Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:38.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi. Please inspect the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:40.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.50,0:10:41.91,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:45.14,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That letter warned that another person on Tsukikage Island
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.14,0:10:48.65,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}would die on the night of a full moon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.65,0:10:54.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's the curse! It's the curse of the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:59.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's no curse. It's this tape recorder that's playing the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:07.06,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This was a murder designed to resemble the previous two incidents!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:08.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:11.20,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey now, don't be getting ahead of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:14.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:18.61,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm a famous detective from Tokyo—Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:21.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, the astronaut?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:24.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No, he's the one in all those mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.35,0:11:26.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's Akechi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:28.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Then who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:34.63,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seawater.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:38.10,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Approximate time of death was\N30 minutes to an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.10,0:11:40.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He probably died of suffocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:43.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My guess is that Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.77,0:11:45.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Drowned by someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:48.84,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I can't say any more without performing an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.84,0:11:51.61,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I think Dr. Narumi is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:53.84,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,See, there's a suit jacket on the beach outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:56.85,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I bet it belongs to Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.85,0:12:01.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's a trail of water here that goes from the door to the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.09,0:12:04.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and there's mud and sand on Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.32,0:12:08.39,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And judging from the fact that the door and windows were all locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:12.86,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and that the first few minutes of the cassette tape are blank...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:15.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,When did he become so—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:19.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The killer probably took Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the ocean during the memorial,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.80,0:12:21.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,drowned him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.24,0:12:23.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,dragged the body into this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.11,0:12:24.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,locked the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:27.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,turned the tape recorder on, and then exited into the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.34,0:12:28.68,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:31.84,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, sounds about right to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.95,0:12:37.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Assuming the door to this room was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:40.26,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,there's a high possibility the killer\Nreturned to the memorial afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.26,0:12:43.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,since we were at the front door the whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.76,0:12:45.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hold on just a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.46,0:12:48.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you saying the killer's still among us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.07,0:12:59.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, the killer is in this very room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.51,0:13:03.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Did anyone here see Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} leave his seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:08.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I saw him. He said he was going to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.22,0:13:11.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Did anybody see anyone else leave their seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.69,0:13:14.79,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,As if we could remember every\Nlittle thing that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.79,0:13:19.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,In that case, did anyone have any\Ngrudges with Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.76,0:13:21.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's not exactly a grudge,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:25.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,but the person most happy about\Nhis death would be Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:28.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,his opponent in the mayoral election!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:32.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?! The same goes for you, Mayor Kuroiwa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.54,0:13:34.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, without Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:36.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Daddy's victory would practically be guaranteed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:38.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,As long as a certain someone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:42.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,wasn't plotting to steal\NKawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s votes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.05,0:13:42.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.89,0:13:44.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Now, now, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:45.96,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Calm down now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.96,0:13:50.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But why did the killer put the body in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:55.10,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Because the killer wanted to place\Nthe blame on the cursed piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:57.90,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Say, just how long has this piano been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.90,0:14:03.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's been here ever since Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} donated it 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:06.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.14,0:14:10.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. His name is even on the keyboard lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:13.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.59,0:14:17.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:21.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's strange. This wasn't here\Nwhen we checked this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:29.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.23,0:14:31.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:33.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He did rather well for himself back in the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:37.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I hear he spent lots of money\Non alcohol, women, and gambling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:40.18,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But after the mayor died 2 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:44.28,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he stopped going out, almost as\Nif he were afraid of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:45.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.02,0:14:49.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wasn't he a childhood friend of yours, Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.12,0:14:52.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose you could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.59,0:14:54.66,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Here's a policeman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:55.89,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're late, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.89,0:15:00.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But I had to look for him;\Nhe wasn't at the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:02.63,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Who called for me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:06.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This gentleman here.\NHis name is Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.54,0:15:07.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, the famous—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.54,0:15:09.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- That's right!\N- Astronaut!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:11.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.91,0:15:14.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,At any rate, it's getting late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.41,0:15:17.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,We can put off collecting information until tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.78,0:15:21.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This was no murder. It was Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:24.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,How horrifying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:28.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They should just burn that creepy old piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:34.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yeah. Maybe we'd be better\Noff without that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.46,0:15:36.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Shuuichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:40.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Your deductions sure surprised me, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.80,0:15:43.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He loves playing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:47.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Everyone was talking about how\Namazing his persuasiveness was!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.21,0:15:49.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I was just pretending to be like Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.35,0:15:52.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I always get to see him at work!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:57.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's just a baby chick compared to me, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.15,0:16:00.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Well, we'll head back to the hotel now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.09,0:16:04.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll see you later then. Please solve\Nthis case as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:07.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'd rather not have to examine any more bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.13,0:16:11.26,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't you worry! This'll be a\Npiece of cake with me at the helm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:17.11,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Whatever. Not even I really\Nknow what's going on yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.74,0:16:19.98,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.98,0:16:23.35,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That letter said, "begin to disappear"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.35,0:16:26.92,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Meaning this isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:30.85,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What? This murder spree has yet to continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.85,0:16:33.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This letter gives warning about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.99,0:16:37.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,"Shadows disappearing" means "being enveloped by light".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:41.93,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Light stands for the song played at\Nall the murder scenes—Moonlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:43.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.33,0:16:47.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The song Mr. Aso played in the fire 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.27,0:16:51.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And the song the mayor played\Nbefore he died 2 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.34,0:16:54.01,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was Beethoven's piano sonata, Moonlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.01,0:16:58.52,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And all three incidents have\Ntaken place beside the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.52,0:17:00.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You two go back to the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:01.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.09,0:17:06.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}! Let's go to the community center too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.56,0:17:12.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're crazy if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:14.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Spending a night with a corpse like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:16.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And with a kid, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.87,0:17:19.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I thought I told you to go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.57,0:17:21.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.44,0:17:25.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Tell me, who moved the body without permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.34,0:17:26.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:31.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I felt bad for the poor guy,\Nbeing stuck in that position...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:32.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You really shouldn't have,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.92,0:17:34.68,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,we're not through investigating the crime scene yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.68,0:17:38.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Huh? The sheet music's gone.\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:42.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, I took that so it wouldn't get lost. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:43.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Stupid old geezer...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.49,0:17:44.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.80,0:17:46.66,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This sheet music is for Moonlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:47.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:48.85,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Moonlight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:58.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What're you doing? You suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.31,0:18:02.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No, this fourth bar is weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.35,0:18:03.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Fourth bar?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.78,0:18:06.28,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Maybe this sheet music is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.28,0:18:08.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.65,0:18:11.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,If so, then the killer might come back for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.69,0:18:13.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:17.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,When I asked for you at the hotel,\Nthey said you were all here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.13,0:18:18.70,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:21.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I brought some dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:23.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.23,0:18:25.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...we could use some food...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.24,0:18:31.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So you're not originally from\Nthis island then, Dr. Narumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.78,0:18:35.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No. I return to Tokyo on the weekends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.11,0:18:37.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's almost like I work as a part-time doctor here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:40.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I've always wanted to work\Non a small island like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.12,0:18:44.25,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,surrounded by nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.25,0:18:46.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I've been working here for 2 years now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:48.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.09,0:18:54.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Did Mayor Kameyama really die\Nof a heart attack two years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:58.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. He had always had heart troubles...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.27,0:19:01.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But his face looked rather convulsive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:04.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,almost as if he saw something horrifying...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.34,0:19:07.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Did you notice anything strange at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.48,0:19:10.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hmm, now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:11.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.65,0:19:13.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I think one of the windows was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:15.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,A window?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.82,0:19:21.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I believe we chalked that up to\Nsomeone forgetting to close it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.02,0:19:22.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Which window was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:24.25,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,If I remember right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.63,0:19:28.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...it was this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.97,0:19:31.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.43,0:19:32.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:33.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.64,0:19:41.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn it! We lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:46.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I was right! He did come back to get this sheet music!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.65,0:19:49.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,OK! We're going to stay up all night\Nand keep watch over this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.19,0:19:49.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Agreed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.99,0:19:51.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Agreed!\N- Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.59,0:19:55.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey. Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:19:57.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:19:58.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-dono{\r}...\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.77,0:20:04.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This island's technically part of Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:06.94,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Where did I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:10.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,If you're looking for the sheet music,\NConan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.14,0:20:12.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He also gave me the gist of the situation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.81,0:20:16.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,All three of them were still\Nawake by the time I arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:20.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You and that old man were the only ones asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:22.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They're interrogating people\Nover at the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.72,0:20:24.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Come give them a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:25.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:39.47,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,We really shouldn't have slept there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.47,0:20:42.47,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dad! Well? Did you figure out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:47.08,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yeah, right. There were\N38 people at the memorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:49.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It won't be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:52.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Sorry, but when will it be my turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.72,0:20:56.25,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You seem exhausted,\Nso you're scheduled to be last.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.25,0:21:00.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,In that case, I think I'll go\Nwash my face in the ladies' room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.46,0:21:03.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,How many more interviewees are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.73,0:21:06.60,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Including Dr. Narumi, there's six:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.60,0:21:10.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The mayor's daughter, Reiko Kuroiwa,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:13.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,her fiancé, Shuuichi Murasawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:15.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,mayoral candidate, Masato Shimizu,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.27,0:21:17.61,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,the mayor's secretary, Kazuaki Hirata,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.61,0:21:21.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and Ken Nishimoto,\Nwho we're interviewing right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.11,0:21:23.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,but he's really wasting our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.55,0:21:25.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He won't say a word, no matter what we ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.75,0:21:28.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My instincts say he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:31.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Idiot! There's no curse on the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.55,0:21:35.06,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,As long as that thing's around,\Nthese murders will keep happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.06,0:21:36.79,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But, Mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.79,0:21:39.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dispose of it immediately! You hear me, Hirata?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:40.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.50,0:21:42.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.37,0:21:47.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I've had enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.44,0:21:51.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I have no motive for killing Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.21,0:21:52.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:54.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wow, listen to Reiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.38,0:21:56.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,She's been shouting for 10 minutes straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.58,0:21:57.85,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.85,0:22:02.99,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}They're through questioning him,\Nso why isn't Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.99,0:22:05.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.22,0:22:07.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I need to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:19.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? Did Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} come in here just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.14,0:22:20.70,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.70,0:22:23.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Crap! He took the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.71,0:22:29.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This music...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.51,0:22:33.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's the second movement of Moonlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.38,0:22:36.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Where's it coming from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.15,0:22:38.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The broadcast room!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.26,0:22:40.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.53,0:22:47.09,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.83,0:22:51.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No, don't go inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.67,0:22:54.97,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Get the examiners and autopsy team here at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.97,0:22:55.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.67,0:22:59.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The autopsy team left for Tokyo this evening to work on Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.44,0:23:00.71,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.71,0:23:02.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn it! Now, of all times!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.55,0:23:04.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.35,0:23:05.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:07.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.35,0:23:10.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But now this narrows down the\Nsuspects to a handful of people!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.92,0:23:13.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So the killer is still—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.02,0:23:16.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,All the exits to this building are guarded by police.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:17.99,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.99,0:23:21.76,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who is it? Who's the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.20,0:23:33.27,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It appears only a few minutes have passed since the victim's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.27,0:23:38.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, the first 5 minutes and 30 seconds of this tape seem to be blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.45,0:23:39.61,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.61,0:23:41.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There was something strange beneath the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.55,0:23:42.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- What?!\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.25,0:23:47.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.05,0:23:50.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Is this another dying message from the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.19,0:23:51.93,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.93,0:23:56.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,If he had the time and strength\Nto write all this with his own blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.13,0:23:57.90,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he would've called for help instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.90,0:24:01.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The killer probably left each of these behind to—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.07,0:24:02.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You stay out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:06.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh no! That's important evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:08.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.81,0:24:11.94,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're in the way! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.08,0:24:20.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seeing as Beethoven's Moonlight Sonata\Nwas played after each murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.09,0:24:29.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,it would seem the same person killed\NKawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:32.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And judging from the amount of blank tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.13,0:24:33.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must have been killed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.77,0:24:37.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,around 6:30, only minutes before he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.57,0:24:40.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,In other words, the killer\Nmust have been one of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.58,0:24:43.71,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,since you were the only ones in\Nthe community center at the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.56,0:24:47.40,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Ken Nishimoto
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.71,0:24:45.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Excluding Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.91,0:24:48.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,that leaves us with Ken Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho was the first to find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.65,0:24:50.90,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Narumi Asai
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:51.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi Asai, who was kind enough\Nto inspect the body for us just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.24,0:24:54.86,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Kazuaki Hirata
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.55,0:24:55.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Kazuaki Hirata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, secretary\Nto the late Mayor Kuroiwa,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.12,0:25:00.37,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Shuichi Murasawa
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.12,0:25:00.37,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Reiko Kuroiwa
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.19,0:24:58.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Mayor Kuroiwa's daughter, Reiko Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.23,0:25:00.66,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and her fiancé, Shuuichi Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.58,0:25:04.29,Character Card,Comment,0,0,0,,Masato Shimizu
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.66,0:25:04.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And then Masato Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Ncandidate in the mayoral election.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.53,0:25:08.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hold on! Why am I a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.07,0:25:12.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You've been questioning me since 6:20!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.21,0:25:15.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're right, you couldn't have done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.58,0:25:18.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Then you can exclude Dr. Narumi too!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.21,0:25:21.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,She's been with us since 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.02,0:25:23.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?\N- Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.15,0:25:27.79,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So that leaves the four men as the only suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.79,0:25:32.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but I've been on\Nthis floor since 6:00 or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.13,0:25:34.83,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Do you have anyone to substantiate this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.83,0:25:38.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You can all vouch for me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.03,0:25:41.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I went to the restroom around 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.77,0:25:44.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Tell me, Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.24,0:25:48.18,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You were the first person to find Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.18,0:25:51.18,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What exactly were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.18,0:25:54.52,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Kuroiwa said he wanted to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.52,0:25:56.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you sure you didn't ask to see him so you could kill him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.78,0:25:58.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.09,0:25:59.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.75,0:26:02.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,With Kawashima and my father taken out of the election,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.56,0:26:07.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he'd automatically wind up in the mayor's seat!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.13,0:26:09.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Oh? What are you looking at, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?\N- Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.80,0:26:13.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- The sheet music the killer left at the murder scene.\N- I would never stoop that low!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.77,0:26:18.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My guess is that it's a coded message from the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.87,0:26:22.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's anything special about these sharps and flats...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.11,0:26:27.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Those are the black keys on the keyboard. You know?{"You know" split off}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.35,0:26:29.22,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Keyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.22,0:26:32.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Arrest this homicidal maniac before he kills anyone else—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.59,0:26:35.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Better watch out. You're next.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.69,0:26:36.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.76,0:26:40.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This code's easy if you know how to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.49,0:26:44.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's based on the notes that correspond with specific piano keys
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.87,0:26:49.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,if you arrange the letters of the alphabet across a piano keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.50,0:26:54.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Using this, the music found where Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed says,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.31,0:27:01.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,"Better watch out. You're next."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.05,0:27:01.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.62,0:27:03.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're amazing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.62,0:27:06.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What does the other sheet music say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.72,0:27:08.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.09,0:27:12.86,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,"Extinguished is the anger of the hellfire."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.86,0:27:16.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The anger of the hellfire?! Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.30,0:27:20.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...that pianist who killed himself in a fire 12 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.87,0:27:28.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's him! Keiji Aso's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.11,0:27:30.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No he isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.48,0:27:34.18,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The bones found in the ashes\Nmatched his dental records.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.18,0:27:36.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's most certainly dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:39.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Everything was completely scorched—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.59,0:27:43.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,all that was left was some\Nsheet music in a fireproof safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.76,0:27:46.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.56,0:27:49.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Where? Where is this sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:51.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,In the community center storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.40,0:27:54.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But the key to the storeroom's back at the station...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.07,0:27:56.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Then go get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.40,0:27:58.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.21,0:28:00.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait, officer! I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.51,0:28:02.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!{add a sheesh after this}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.91,0:28:08.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Say, did Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really set his own house on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.38,0:28:12.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, there were four eyewitnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.29,0:28:14.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Our previous mayor, Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.19,0:28:18.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Mayor Kuroiwa, Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.56,0:28:20.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Were those four connected in any way?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.43,0:28:24.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They were all classmates, including Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.73,0:28:27.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Then what about that Murasawa guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.54,0:28:32.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He showed up on the island 3 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.57,0:28:36.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He and the mayor's daughter Reiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were engaged not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.41,0:28:38.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The mayor opposed it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.78,0:28:41.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What about Hirata, the mayor's secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.62,0:28:43.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's suspicious if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.92,0:28:45.95,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm not quite sure what the deal was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.95,0:28:48.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,but he was always sneaking around with Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.19,0:28:50.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,at the community center.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.29,0:28:52.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What about Shimizu?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.46,0:28:56.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He has a strong sense of justice and\Nhe's very popular with the fishermen!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.13,0:29:02.94,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you out of questions, Akechi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.94,0:29:04.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.94,0:29:08.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? That's odd!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.74,0:29:11.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I could swear it was around here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.91,0:29:16.08,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come on. You've been looking for over an hour now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.08,0:29:20.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Here we go! Here's the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.19,0:29:22.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.49,0:29:24.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.12,0:29:25.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You took too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.33,0:29:27.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Everyone grew tired of waiting\Nso they went home!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.80,0:29:30.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,All the suspects left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.13,0:29:31.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.13,0:29:36.24,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The killer's last message said that\Nthe hellfire's anger was extinguished,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.24,0:29:38.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,so they figured there would be no more murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.87,0:29:40.11,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Idiots!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.11,0:29:42.41,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only the 1st and 2nd movements of Moonlight have been played
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:45.41,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}at each of the murder scenes so far!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.41,0:29:48.82,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Moonlight has one movement left!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.82,0:29:51.28,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm going to check out the community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.35,0:29:55.15,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.96,0:30:00.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Talk about curious, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.36,0:30:01.86,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.86,0:30:03.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Just hold on, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.57,0:30:09.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Did you just hear a strange sound\Ncome from the piano room?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.04,0:30:11.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.41,0:30:12.93,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.51,0:30:17.84,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.22,0:30:24.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,M-Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.05,0:30:25.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.29,0:30:26.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The storeroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.72,0:30:32.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.16,0:30:34.86,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Officer! Go call Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.86,0:30:36.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.63,0:30:42.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Was the 3rd movement played?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.00,0:30:43.94,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's 30 minutes per side on this tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.94,0:30:47.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,which means Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ndied within the last 30 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.81,0:30:48.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Look, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.91,0:30:51.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's some more sheet music\Nat Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.62,0:30:58.39,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What does it say this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.39,0:30:59.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,"Will".
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.75,0:31:01.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's his will?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.49,0:31:03.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Then does that mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.92,0:31:05.93,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,—it was a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.93,0:31:07.26,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,According to the will,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.26,0:31:10.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he regretted killing\NMr. Kawashima and Mr. Kuroiwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.76,0:31:12.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Nishimoto killed the two of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.40,0:31:17.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He apparently didn't want an old mistake they made to be made known.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.77,0:31:21.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,"They" refers to Mr. Kameyama, who died 2 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.04,0:31:24.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Mr. Kawashima and Mr. Kuroiwa, who were just killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.04,0:31:26.05,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Mr. Nishimoto, who hanged himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.05,0:31:29.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and Mr. Aso, who killed himself 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.22,0:31:31.39,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The pianist too?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.39,0:31:35.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My guess is that they did something, using this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.29,0:31:39.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I see. Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was afraid their old secret would get out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.76,0:31:42.96,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,so he broke into the storeroom to destroy the sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.96,0:31:45.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But unable to find the music and driven into a psychological corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.80,0:31:47.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.74,0:31:50.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I don't think it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.74,0:31:54.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's impossible to hang yourself without something to support you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.14,0:31:56.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you sure you didn't put it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.54,0:31:58.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.45,0:32:03.95,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And I doubt there's anyone who would\Ngo and write their own will in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.95,0:32:07.49,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you saying the murderer is somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.49,0:32:10.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- I saw some suspicious people.\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.22,0:32:11.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Two people in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.99,0:32:14.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,One broke a window and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.23,0:32:16.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The other was that Murasawa guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.23,0:32:17.60,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Someone beat him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.60,0:32:21.83,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi's treating him in\Nthe piano room right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.24,0:32:24.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.44,0:32:25.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say that sooner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.77,0:32:28.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.04,0:32:31.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You still haven't found Mr. Aso's sheet music?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.81,0:32:36.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was 12 years ago; there's no way for me to remember where we put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.72,0:32:40.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Is he still unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.69,0:32:44.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. I think he may have suffered a concussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.12,0:32:45.69,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Say, Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.69,0:32:49.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What was Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} doing here this late anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.80,0:32:51.96,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,How should I know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.47,0:32:55.90,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.90,0:32:58.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Keep your hands off Shuuichi's stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.07,0:32:59.44,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.44,0:33:03.41,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't ask me! But it was important to Shuuichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.41,0:33:07.48,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's a tuning hammer, used to tune pianos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.48,0:33:09.58,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}So he was the one who—
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.58,0:33:13.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,OK! Bring all the suspects\Nto the town hall at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.99,0:33:14.92,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.06,0:33:22.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.56,0:33:23.83,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's go to the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.83,0:33:26.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The suspicious person who ran out of this room
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.50,0:33:30.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,was looking for something under the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.04,0:33:32.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Here we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.11,0:33:36.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Wow, a hidden panel! Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.61,0:33:42.38,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Drugs!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.15,0:33:46.73,Signs,Comment,0,0,0,,Tsukikage Island Town Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.19,0:33:49.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Judging from the methods\Nemployed in all three murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.56,0:33:52.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,they are all clearly the work of the same person!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.56,0:33:56.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi and Reiko Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nhave confirmed alibis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.33,0:33:58.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and are no longer suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.23,0:34:01.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But there are no alibis for\Nthe secretary Hirata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.07,0:34:03.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,the mayoral candidate Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.54,0:34:07.31,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,nor for Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho is currently resting at the clinic...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.31,0:34:10.48,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The killer is one of these three!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.48,0:34:12.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi. Is Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} still unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.78,0:34:16.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. Reiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is looking after him,\Nbut he has yet to regain consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.82,0:34:21.36,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's something nagging at me, but what could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.36,0:34:27.56,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ever since I saw the code of blood\Nleft at the scene of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.56,0:34:28.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.30,0:34:31.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The photos taken from where\NMr. Kuroiwa was murdered are ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.23,0:34:34.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Good. Place them on that desk.\N- Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.51,0:34:43.18,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's that light by Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.18,0:34:46.45,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's off in the picture where he's been moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.45,0:34:51.95,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Um, may I buy some juice? I'm thirsty...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.95,0:34:54.22,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I suppose that'd be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.22,0:34:55.78,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.96,0:35:01.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Say, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.76,0:35:04.16,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,There's some white powder on your sleeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.16,0:35:06.36,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.20,0:35:10.20,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Money from all over the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.20,0:35:13.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm fond of foreign countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.22,0:35:23.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.12,0:35:27.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I finally found the sheet music\NAso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.55,0:35:29.25,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Let me see that!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.89,0:35:35.90,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}"To my son, Seiji."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.90,0:35:37.13,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.13,0:35:43.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, come to think of it, Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a son too...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.50,0:35:47.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He fell seriously ill when he was little\Nand had to be hospitalized...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.54,0:35:51.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I believe Seiji was his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.21,0:35:52.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seiji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.65,0:35:54.88,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.45,0:36:03.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey, wait! Where do you think you're going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.30,0:36:12.53,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.53,0:36:14.67,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The reason the killer dragged Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.67,0:36:17.07,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}after drowning him!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.07,0:36:19.44,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The meaning of the music played at the murder scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.44,0:36:23.44,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the mystery behind the code written in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.44,0:36:27.78,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no doubt about it!\NThat's the one who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.35,0:36:34.99,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Old man Mouri received a letter from a dead man
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.99,0:36:37.12,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}and then headed to Tsukikage Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.12,0:36:40.79,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The letter's author was Keiji Aso, a pianist who murdered his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.79,0:36:45.73,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}lit his house on fire, and died while playing the Moonlight piano sonata.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.73,0:36:48.50,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The first murder happened on the night of the memorial for Mr. Kameyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.50,0:36:50.47,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}the previous mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.47,0:36:52.74,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hideo Kawashima was found dead in the piano room,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.74,0:36:55.98,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}while the first movement of Moonlight played.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.98,0:36:59.98,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The second murder took place\Nas the second movement played.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.98,0:37:02.62,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim was the current\Nmayor, Tatsuji Kuroiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.62,0:37:04.85,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The number of suspects was\Nnarrowed down to six people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.85,0:37:08.06,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The third murder was that of Ken Nishimoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.06,0:37:10.35,Narration Off,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}He was killed in a manner\Nthat made it look like suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.89,0:37:16.96,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}"To my son, Seiji."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.96,0:37:19.43,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.43,0:37:21.57,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The reason the killer dragged Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.57,0:37:24.10,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}after drowning him!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.10,0:37:26.67,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The meaning of the music played at the murder scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.67,0:37:30.64,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the mystery behind the code written in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.64,0:37:34.51,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no doubt about it!\NThat's the one who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.85,0:37:40.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What's the big idea, rushing here\Nto the broadcast room like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.99,0:37:43.12,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Is there something here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.12,0:37:45.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.23,0:37:49.46,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got no choice! I'll have to\Nuse the old man's voice for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.46,0:37:51.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,One shot of this Tranquilizer Watch Gun and...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.80,0:37:57.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hirata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will have to come to the mainland with us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.87,0:37:59.07,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.07,0:38:00.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.67,0:38:03.64,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The first incident, in which Mr. Kawashima was drowned
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.64,0:38:07.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and dragged into the community center's piano room last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.35,0:38:09.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The second incident, in which Mr. Kuroiwa was murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.82,0:38:12.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,in the broadcast room this very night...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.75,0:38:15.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The third incident, which also took place this very night,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.76,0:38:17.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,in which Mr. Nishimoto was killed in the storeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.56,0:38:20.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,in such a way to make it look like a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.09,0:38:23.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The only ones without alibis for these three incidents are you two
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.43,0:38:27.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is resting at the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.67,0:38:30.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to do this, but we'll\Nhave to watch you tonight—
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.77,0:38:33.81,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've figured it out, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.81,0:38:36.88,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Almost everything about the\Nmurders on this island, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.88,0:38:39.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dad! You're in the broadcast room?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.11,0:38:43.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,First, the person who beat Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} unconscious in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.45,0:38:47.29,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That would be you, Hirata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!{at "Hirata-san", switch to radio style}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.29,0:38:48.39,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.39,0:38:50.72,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hirata{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10} suffered the injury on his left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.72,0:38:53.59,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}when he broke the window and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.59,0:38:56.63,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}You were also the suspicious\Nperson we saw last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.63,0:38:58.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But what was he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.73,0:39:03.17,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He was making deals with\NMr. Kawashima in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.17,0:39:04.34,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Drug deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.34,0:39:06.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Drugs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.21,0:39:08.88,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hirata{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10} used a hidden panel in the piano
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.88,0:39:14.18,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}to trade drugs he bought overseas for large sums of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.18,0:39:20.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Aha! So that's why they were at the\Ncommunity center every single night!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.32,0:39:24.42,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The reason Hirata{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10} always\Nclaimed the piano was cursed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.42,0:39:27.43,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}was to keep people from getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.43,0:39:29.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He probably assaulted Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and escaped
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.46,0:39:33.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,because Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw him\Ntaking back the drugs he had left there!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.80,0:39:34.84,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Does that mean you killed Mr. Kawashima
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.84,0:39:38.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,because you were having a dispute with him about the deals?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.04,0:39:39.37,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.37,0:39:43.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Hirata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has nothing to do\Nwith the three murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.11,0:39:47.15,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}If he was the murderer, he wouldn't have killed anyone in the piano room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.15,0:39:51.62,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was the room where\Nhe left the drugs, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.62,0:39:53.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Next is Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.72,0:39:55.49,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.49,0:39:58.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's not the killer either.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.99,0:40:02.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The reason the killer wrote\Na will to make it look a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.40,0:40:04.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,but didn't place an object to stand on in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.33,0:40:06.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,was because the murderer bolted\Nwhen Ran and the others showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.80,0:40:09.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It would have been impossible to\Nenter the piano room afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.67,0:40:11.74,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.74,0:40:14.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So far, our image of the killer\Nhas been that of a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.21,0:40:17.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,because all three murders required someone with strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.51,0:40:20.65,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And someone without an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.65,0:40:23.75,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The only suspect left is Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.75,0:40:27.09,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Next, we need to look at the second murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.09,0:40:31.46,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,We assumed Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed\Nonly minutes before he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.46,0:40:33.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But if you'll remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.53,0:40:40.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...the blood code didn't come off\Nwhen Conan fell on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.53,0:40:45.71,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,At room temperature, it takes 15 to\N30 minutes for human blood to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.71,0:40:49.14,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But that blood was dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.14,0:40:52.18,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}even though he was supposedly killed only minutes before.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.18,0:40:58.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's right. It was a trick the killer did\Nto alter the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.99,0:41:00.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.72,0:41:05.06,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But only the first 5 and a half minutes of the tape were blank!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.06,0:41:06.59,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Automatic tape reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.59,0:41:09.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The killer played the 2nd side of the tape—\Nwhich had no music on it—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.80,0:41:13.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and gained 30 extra minutes by using tape reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.77,0:41:15.94,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please have a look at the photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.94,0:41:19.11,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a button lit near Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.11,0:41:22.41,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the light is off just after his body is moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.41,0:41:27.41,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's proof that the killer turned\Nit off when you weren't looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.41,0:41:30.78,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But if I remember correctly, the one who approached the body was—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.78,0:41:32.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.09,0:41:34.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The person who got near the body,\Naside from the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.45,0:41:36.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,The person who faked the estimated time of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:42.28,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,...was the one who inspected the body: you, Dr. Narumi!{"you, Dr. Narumi" in radio style}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.33,0:41:47.03,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,That's not true, is it, Dr. Narumi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.33,0:41:52.91,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You drowned Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand dragged him into the piano room
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.91,0:41:55.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,in order to send the coroners back to the mainland,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.11,0:41:58.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,since they wouldn't be able to\Nexamine an unnatural death here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.58,0:42:02.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,And the reason you put blank space\Nat the start of each tape
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.32,0:42:06.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,was so that you could throw us off\Nby faking the time of the 2nd murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.72,0:42:10.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Doing this, you altered Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s time of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.82,0:42:13.33,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,thereby creating an alibi for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.33,0:42:17.70,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! You just said the killer was a man!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.70,0:42:20.60,Radio,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The motive for the murders extends 12 years back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.60,0:42:22.50,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.50,0:42:26.67,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Back to the incident in which pianist\NKeiji Aso and his family were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.67,0:42:28.54,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.54,0:42:31.38,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Kawashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Nishimoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kuroiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.38,0:42:34.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,and the previous mayor, Kameyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.35,0:42:36.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They used Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s international performances
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.35,0:42:39.72,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,as opportunities to buy and sell drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.72,0:42:44.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But then Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he refused to help them any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.19,0:42:46.83,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Afraid their secret would get out,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.83,0:42:51.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,they shut him and his family inside his house and set it on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.87,0:42:57.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This is all written in the sheet music that survived that fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.77,0:43:01.81,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,In the confession letter that Aso{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wrote for his child...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.81,0:43:03.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,A son?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.11,0:43:07.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He had a son in a Tokyo hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.55,0:43:09.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,One named Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.45,0:43:12.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seiji? It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.45,0:43:15.62,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dr. Narumi's real name is Seiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.05,0:43:19.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Narumi Asai
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.84,0:43:19.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seiji Aso
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.62,0:43:19.09,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,She was Keiji Aso's son, Seiji Aso!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.09,0:43:21.80,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.80,0:43:26.60,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Asai is probably his foster family's last name.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.60,0:43:31.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,So it was all to avenge his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.04,0:43:33.57,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- Inspector! The killer's gone!\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.57,0:43:36.04,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.04,0:43:37.14,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know where he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.14,0:43:40.94,Thoughts,Comment,0,0,0,,{\be10}The place where Aso Keiji's donated piano is kept: the community center!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.66,0:43:52.02,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's over, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.53,0:43:55.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.43,0:43:58.00,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Here, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.00,0:44:01.43,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's written in this sheet music your dad left for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.43,0:44:05.51,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He says he wants you to live an honest life!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.51,0:44:08.58,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I wish I had known that sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.58,0:44:13.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,How did you find out about your father if you haven't read this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.45,0:44:17.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I always had my suspicions about my foster father.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.35,0:44:18.82,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,After graduating from medical school,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.82,0:44:22.86,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I came to this island as a woman doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.86,0:44:28.40,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It doesn't say on my license how\Nto pronounce my name, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.40,0:44:31.70,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,But I was sweating bullets when\Nthey started questioning people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.70,0:44:33.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,They would've found out I was really a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.77,0:44:37.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I see. So that's why you stayed with us that night—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.87,0:44:41.37,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,so you could have them question you last.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.37,0:44:46.28,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,When I told Kameyama, the previous mayor, that I was Aso's son,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.28,0:44:49.42,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,he suddenly grew fearful and told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.42,0:44:53.19,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He finished it all off by falling lifeless from a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.19,0:44:58.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It was when I played my father's favorite piece, Moonlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.32,0:45:01.35,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,as a farewell song for him that I came\Nup with the idea for these murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.43,0:45:05.73,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Seiji! Let's get out of here! We can still make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.73,0:45:08.87,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,It's too late for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.87,0:45:14.53,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,These hands are as bloodstained as theirs are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.98,0:45:20.11,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.11,0:45:20.88,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.88,0:45:24.45,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,- No!\N- Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.45,0:45:27.55,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.55,0:45:29.79,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,This is the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.79,0:45:34.56,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,He's playing it. Inside the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.04,0:45:47.94,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Murasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} missed Keiji Aso, the pianist,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.94,0:45:51.21,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,so he apparently tuned his piano on occasion...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.21,0:45:53.77,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,On the night he was assaulted, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.12,0:45:59.32,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Why did Dr. Narumi warn us about the murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.32,0:46:02.99,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,My only guess is that it was actually a letter of challenge to Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.99,0:46:06.76,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,I think she wanted to be stopped from killing...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.76,0:46:11.30,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Say, what did the code that Dr. Narumi played say?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.30,0:46:13.23,Dialogue,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh, I already forgot.
